# {{ .ProjectName }} - EVM Token Toolkit

A comprehensive token management toolkit built with Solidity ^0.8.20 and Foundry. All contracts are standalone with no external dependencies.

## Contracts

### ManagedToken (ERC-20)
Full-featured ERC-20 token with owner-controlled minting, user burn, and pause functionality.

- **Mint** -- Owner can mint new tokens to any address
- **Burn** -- Any holder can burn their own tokens
- **Pause/Unpause** -- Owner can pause all transfers in an emergency
- **Ownership Transfer** -- Owner can transfer control to a new address

### VestingSchedule
Linear token vesting with cliff support. Designed for team allocations, advisor grants, and contributor rewards.

- **Create schedules** with configurable start, cliff period, and total duration
- **Linear vesting** after the cliff -- tokens unlock proportionally over time
- **Release** vested tokens at any time after cliff
- **Revoke** unvested tokens (owner only) -- vested portion goes to beneficiary, rest returns to owner

### StakeRewards
Proportional staking rewards distribution based on the Synthetix staking model.

- **Stake** tokens to earn rewards proportional to your share of the pool
- **Withdraw** staked tokens at any time
- **Claim** accumulated rewards
- **Configurable** reward rate and duration period

### MultiSig
M-of-N multisignature wallet for secure fund management and governance.

- **Submit** transactions (ETH transfers or arbitrary contract calls)
- **Confirm** pending transactions (each owner gets one vote)
- **Execute** when the required threshold is met
- **Revoke** confirmations before execution
- **Receive** ETH directly via receive/fallback

## Project Structure

```
contracts/
  token/ManagedToken.sol        -- ERC-20 with mint, burn, pause
  vesting/VestingSchedule.sol   -- Linear vesting with cliff
  staking/StakeRewards.sol      -- Stake-to-earn rewards
  multisig/MultiSig.sol         -- M-of-N multisig wallet
test/
  token/ManagedToken.t.sol      -- Token tests
  vesting/VestingSchedule.t.sol -- Vesting tests
  staking/StakeRewards.t.sol    -- Staking tests
  multisig/MultiSig.t.sol       -- Multisig tests
scripts/
  deploy-token.js               -- Deploy ManagedToken
  setup-vesting.js              -- Deploy vesting + create example schedules
```

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Foundry](https://book.getfoundry.sh/getting-started/installation) (forge, cast, anvil)
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) >= 18 (for deployment scripts)
- ethers.js v6 (`npm install ethers`)

### Build

```bash
forge build
```

### Test

```bash
forge test -vvv
```

### Deploy

1. Start a local node:
   ```bash
   anvil
   ```

2. Deploy the token:
   ```bash
   export PRIVATE_KEY="0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80"
   export RPC_URL="http://127.0.0.1:8545"
   export TOKEN_NAME="MyToken"
   export TOKEN_SYMBOL="MTK"
   export INITIAL_SUPPLY="1000000"
   node scripts/deploy-token.js
   ```

3. Set up vesting schedules:
   ```bash
   export TOKEN_ADDRESS="<address from step 2>"
   node scripts/setup-vesting.js
   ```

## Configuration

The `foundry.toml` configures:
- Solidity 0.8.20 compiler
- Optimizer enabled with 200 runs
- Shanghai EVM target
- Source in `contracts/`, tests in `test/`

